objects.name: speccom
objects.description: SpecCom is a malicious 32-bit Windows executable that uses HTTP for communication. It has command and control (C2) over HTTP with tasking within HTML comment tags. Tasking is Base64-encoded with multiple layers of XOR obfuscation. Capability includes uploading of data and execution of Windows commands.

objects.name: SpecCom Threat Actor
objects.description: The threat actor behind SpecCom is not explicitly mentioned in the report, but it is assessed to be relatively low-sophistication malware.
